### FORGE CLI (Spec 130)

The `bin/forge` script provides a CLI entry point for any AI agent or CI pipeline:

```bash
bin/forge <command> [spec-number] [--plain|--json]
```

The CLI auto-detects the active agent runtime (Claude Code, Aider, generic) and dispatches
accordingly. Use `--plain` to output the assembled prompt to stdout for piping to any LLM CLI.
Use `--json` for structured output suitable for CI/script consumption.

On Windows, use `bin\forge.ps1` for native PowerShell support.

